From 98b93c97ad00bd5faa136f4ac51c74293a96a08f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Michael Henke <henke.mike@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 16:23:52 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 02/10] fix: notify orchestrator when background child tasks
 complete (#765)

Part 1 - phantom + completion swallow during fallback:
- pending-call-tracker: add peek() (non-consuming read)
- session.created net: take->peek (preserves pending call for
  tool.execute.after) + drop stale phantom running jobs on fallback

Part 2 - orchestrator not notified of completion:
- message transform: replace existing board part text instead of
  skipping, so re-injections show fresh completions
- add onTerminalJob callback, fired when a child job reaches a
  terminal state (guarded by shouldManageSession)
- wire onTerminalJob to client.session.promptAsync to prod the
  orchestrator into a new turn on child completion

Regression test added in task-session-manager/index.test.ts.
